# blackfoot sky culture name
msgid "Blackfoot"
msgstr "kaki hitam"

# blackfoot sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"The Blackfoot is an Algonquian-speaking tribe living in the northern Great\n"
"Plains of North America."
msgstr ""
"The Blackfoot adalah suku berbahasa Algonquian yang tinggal di Great Plains "
"utara Amerika Utara."

# blackfoot sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"This sky culture has 4 constellation line figures, and names for the Milky Way,\n"
"the Pleiades, the Orion Nebula, three planets and three stars.\n"
"\n"
"According to the sources, the Blackfoot often featured the Big Dipper, the\n"
"Pleiades, and the Morning Star on their tipis, and believe that \"when people\n"
"die, their spirits go into the sky and become stars, thus ever increasing the\n"
"number of stars in the heavens\".\n"
"\n"
"### Constellations and star names\n"
"\n"
"The constellation `Seven Brothers and Their Sister` (identified with the\n"
"Western Big Dipper) represents siblings who escape to the sky when being chased\n"
"by a bear. The sister is the small star Alcor in one version. This is the\n"
"version written here: the source doesn't explicitly provide the constellation\n"
"lines, but identifies it with the modern Big Dipper, as a bowl with a handle,\n"
"so Alcor is not connected by a line, but is part of the constellation. Two\n"
"stars are named: the `Little Sister`, also named as `Sinopa` (translated\n"
"`Kit-Fox`)[#3], and \"the star at the end of the handle is often called\n"
"`Last Brother`\" [#1]. This constellation was used for time-keeping before the\n"
"introduction of clocks.\n"
"\n"
"In a second version of this constellation, the youngest brother becomes the\n"
"North Star, and the sister (who used to carry him) is the pointer star at the\n"
"lip of the bowl.\n"
"\n"
"The two main stars in Gemini (Castor and Pollux) are `Ashes-Chief and\n"
"Stuck-Behind`, twins whose story explains how a particular tipi design came\n"
"into use.\n"
"\n"
"The `Lodge of the Spider Man` is the brightest six stars of the Western\n"
"Northern Crown, representing the stones laid in a circle which used to hold\n"
"down a tipi. The `Spider Man's Fingers` is a possible configuration of stars in\n"
"Hercules[#1], so its structure is uncertain; they would represent five\n"
"fingers spinning a thread to let the legendary Feather Woman (native name:\n"
"So-at-sa-ki) down from the sky (\"the five bright stars just beyond [the\n"
"Northern Crown] in the constellation of Hercules are his five fingers\" [#3]).\n"
"\n"
"The six stars of the Pleiades (called `Lost Children` or `Bunched Stars`)\n"
"represent six poor children and have an associated story which explains why\n"
"they are visible in the evening sky only from fall to spring, but not the rest\n"
"of the year.\n"
"\n"
"A constellation called `Hand in the Sky` has been documented, but not\n"
"identified (so is not in this dataset). It could be another name for the\n"
"`Spider Man's Fingers`, or another constellation entirely. An associated story\n"
"also explains a particular tipi design.\n"
"\n"
"The North Star is called the `Star that Stands Still` (the other stars walk\n"
"around it).\n"
"\n"
"### Planets\n"
"\n"
"Jupiter is known as `Young Morning Star`, representing a boy, `Poïa`. Venus is\n"
"known as `Morning Star`, the boy's father. A story explains that they sometimes\n"
"travel together, but they may also travel apart for many years. At the time\n"
"when this story was documented (in July 1905), they were in conjunction. The\n"
"names for Mars are not explained in the source.\n"
"\n"
"### Other sky objects\n"
"\n"
"The Milky Way is called the `Wolf Trail`, which represents the shortest path\n"
"from the sky to the earth. The Orion Nebula is the stone knife of the mythical\n"
"person `Blood-Clot`, \"a culture hero who rids the world of evil\" [#1], and is\n"
"also called `Smoking-Star`."
msgstr ""
"Budaya langit ini memiliki 4 figur garis konstelasi, dan nama untuk Bima Sakti, Pleiades, Nebula Orion, tiga planet, dan tiga bintang.\n"
"\n"
"Menurut sumber, Blackfoot sering menampilkan Biduk, Pleiades, dan Bintang Kejora pada tipis mereka, dan percaya bahwa \"ketika orang mati, roh mereka pergi ke langit dan menjadi bintang, sehingga semakin meningkatkan jumlah bintang di surga\".\n"
"\n"
"### Rasi bintang dan nama bintang\n"
"\n"
"Rasi bintang `Seven Brothers and They Sister` (diidentifikasi dengan Biduk Barat) mewakili saudara kandung yang melarikan diri ke langit ketika dikejar oleh beruang. Adiknya adalah bintang kecil Alcor dalam satu versi. Ini adalah versi yang ditulis di sini: sumbernya tidak secara eksplisit memberikan garis konstelasi, tetapi mengidentifikasinya dengan Biduk modern, sebagai mangkuk dengan pegangan, jadi Alcor tidak dihubungkan oleh garis, tetapi merupakan bagian dari konstelasi. Dua bintang diberi nama: `Little Sister`, juga disebut sebagai `Sinopa` (diterjemahkan\n"
"`Kit-Fox`)[#3], dan \"bintang di ujung pegangan sering disebut\n"
"`Last Brother`\" [#1]. Rasi bintang ini digunakan untuk menjaga waktu sebelum pengenalan jam.\n"
"\n"
"Dalam versi kedua dari konstelasi ini, saudara bungsu menjadi Bintang Utara, dan saudara perempuan (yang biasa menggendongnya) adalah bintang penunjuk di bibir mangkuk.\n"
"\n"
"Dua bintang utama di Gemini (Castor dan Pollux) adalah `Ashes-Chief dan Stuck-Behind`, kembar yang ceritanya menjelaskan bagaimana desain tipi tertentu mulai digunakan.\n"
"\n"
"`Lodge of the Spider Man` adalah enam bintang paling terang di Western Northern Crown, mewakili batu-batu yang diletakkan dalam lingkaran yang digunakan untuk menahan tipi. `Jari Manusia Laba-laba` adalah kemungkinan konfigurasi bintang di Hercules[#1], jadi strukturnya tidak pasti; mereka akan mewakili lima jari yang memutar seutas benang untuk membiarkan Wanita Bulu yang legendaris (nama asli: So-at-sa-ki) turun dari langit (\"lima bintang terang tepat di luar [Mahkota Utara] di konstelasi Hercules adalah miliknya lima jari\" [#3]).\n"
"\n"
"Enam bintang Pleiades (disebut `Anak Hilang` atau `Bintang Berkumpul`) mewakili enam anak miskin dan memiliki cerita terkait yang menjelaskan mengapa mereka terlihat di langit malam hanya dari musim gugur hingga musim semi, tetapi tidak sepanjang tahun. .\n"
"\n"
"Sebuah konstelasi yang disebut `Hand in the Sky` telah didokumentasikan, tetapi tidak diidentifikasi (begitu juga tidak dalam kumpulan data ini). Itu bisa menjadi nama lain untuk\n"
"`Spider Man's Fingers`, atau konstelasi lain seluruhnya. Sebuah cerita terkait juga menjelaskan desain tipi tertentu.\n"
"\n"
"Bintang Utara disebut `Bintang yang Berdiri Diam` (bintang-bintang lain berjalan mengelilinginya).\n"
"\n"
"### Planet\n"
"\n"
"Jupiter dikenal sebagai `Bintang Kejora Muda`, mewakili seorang anak laki-laki, `Poïa`. Venus dikenal sebagai 'Bintang Kejora', ayah dari anak itu. Sebuah cerita menjelaskan bahwa mereka terkadang bepergian bersama, tetapi mereka juga dapat bepergian secara terpisah selama bertahun-tahun. Pada saat cerita ini didokumentasikan (pada Juli 1905), mereka sedang berhubungan. Nama-nama Mars tidak dijelaskan dalam sumbernya.\n"
"\n"
"### Benda langit lainnya\n"
"\n"
"Bima Sakti disebut `Wolf Trail`, yang mewakili jalur terpendek dari langit ke bumi. Nebula Orion adalah pisau batu dari orang mitos `Blood-Clot`, \"pahlawan budaya yang menyingkirkan dunia dari kejahatan\" [#1], dan juga disebut `Smoking-Star`."

# blackfoot sky culture extras section in markdown format
msgid ""
"This sky culture for Stellarium is a transcript of the broad survey of\n"
"North-American astronomical traditions in the book `Stars of the first people:\n"
"Native American star myths and constellations` [#1] (from page 243). The basic\n"
"information is not collected by this recent author. It is attributed to\n"
"anthropologists from the early 1900s: `Mythology of the Blackfoot Indians`\n"
"published in 1908 [#2], and `The old north trail, or, Life, legends and\n"
"religion of the Blackfeet Indians` published in 1910 [#3]. Source [#1] instead\n"
"collects the data and draws the constellations explicitly, based on the early\n"
"information in [#2] and [#3].\n"
"\n"
"The sources include many associated star stories (not transcribed here), and\n"
"mostly English names."
msgstr ""
"Budaya langit untuk Stellarium ini adalah transkrip survei luas tradisi astronomi Amerika Utara dalam buku `Bintang orang pertama: mitos dan konstelasi bintang asli Amerika` [#1] (dari halaman 243). Informasi dasar tidak dikumpulkan oleh penulis baru-baru ini. Hal ini dikaitkan dengan antropolog dari awal 1900-an: `Mitologi Blackfoot Indians` diterbitkan pada tahun 1908 [#2], dan `The old north trail, or, Life, legends and religion of the Blackfeet Indians` diterbitkan pada tahun 1910 [#3]. Sumber [#1] malah mengumpulkan data dan menggambar konstelasi secara eksplisit, berdasarkan informasi awal di [#2] dan [#3].\n"
"\n"
"Sumbernya mencakup banyak kisah bintang terkait (tidak ditranskripsikan di sini), dan sebagian besar nama dalam bahasa Inggris."

# blackfoot sky culture references section in markdown format
msgid ""
" - [#1]: Dorcas S. Miller. Stars of the first people: Native American star myths and constellations. Westwinds Press, 1997.\n"
" - [#2]: Clark Wissler and D. C. Duvall. Mythology of the Blackfoot Indians. Published by the American Museum of Natural History, New York. 1908. Available at <https://archive.org/details/mythologyofblack00wiss> (accessed Jan 2022).\n"
" - [#3]: Walter McClintock. The old North trail, or, Life, legends and religion of the Blackfeet Indians. Macmillan and Co., Limited, London. 1910. Available at <https://archive.org/details/oldnorthtrailorl00mccluoft> (accessed Jan 2022).\n"
" - [#4]: Doina Bucur. The network signature of constellation line figures. arXiv e-prints. arXiv:2110.12329 [cs.SI]. 2021. Available at <https://arxiv.org/abs/2110.12329>."
msgstr ""
" - [#1]: Dorcas S. Miller. Bintang orang pertama: Mitos dan rasi bintang penduduk asli Amerika. Westwinds Press, 1997.\n"
" - [#2]: Clark Wissler dan D. C. Duvall. Mitologi Indian Blackfoot. Diterbitkan oleh Museum Sejarah Alam Amerika, New York. 1908. Tersedia di <https://archive.org/details/mythologyofblack00wiss> (diakses Jan 2022).\n"
" - [#3]: Walter McClintock. Jejak Utara lama, atau, Kehidupan, legenda dan agama orang Indian Blackfeet. Macmillan and Co., Limited, London. 1910. Tersedia di <https://archive.org/details/oldnorthtrailorl00mccluoft> (diakses Jan 2022).\n"
" - [#4]: Doina Bucur. Tanda tangan jaringan figur garis konstelasi. arXiv e-print. arXiv:2110.12329 [cs.SI]. 2021. Tersedia di <https://arxiv.org/abs/2110.12329>."

