# egyptian sky culture name
msgid "Egyptian"
msgstr "Mesir"

# egyptian sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"The late Egyptian sky culture was influenced by Babylonian and Greco-Roman\n"
"astronomy. Constellations are depicted on the famous astronomical ceiling from\n"
"Denderah."
msgstr ""
"Budaya langit Mesir akhir dipengaruhi oleh astronomi Babilonia dan Yunani-"
"Romawi. Rasi bintang digambarkan di langit-langit astronomi yang terkenal "
"dari Denderah."

# egyptian sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"The belief that the stars could influence human destinies appears to not have\n"
"reached Egypt until the Ptolemaic period. The temple of Hathor at Denderah\n"
"dates from Ptolemaic times (probably the first century BCE) and features a\n"
"wonderful and huge symbolic map of the sky in Egyptian painting style.\n"
"\n"
"It provides two versions: a circular shaped one [#10] and a rectangularly shaped\n"
"one [#11]. The rectangular \"zodiac\" of Denderah shows a sequence of Egyptian\n"
"figures next to a set of symbolic stars indicating how many stars form each\n"
"constellations. The round \"zodiac\" organizes these figures as if they were\n"
"placed in the sky.\n"
"\n"
"![](dendera_zodiac.webp)\n"
"One of the first depictions of the Dendera \"zodiac\", produced by\n"
"engineer-archaeologists Prosper Jollois and Edouard Devilliers in the 19th\n"
"century. The large figure on the right is the Goddess of Heaven, Nut. First\n"
"published in: Description de l'Égypte Antiquités, v. 4 [#12]\n"
"{: .img_and_caption }\n"
"\n"
"These constellations deviate in naming and depiction from the typical Greek\n"
"style:\n"
"\n"
" * Cancer, the Crab, is represented by the Scarab Beetle.\n"
" * the Big Dipper is not called Bear but \"the Bull's Foreleg\" refering to the\n"
"Foreleg of God Seth, an ancient Egyptian constellation\n"
" * The figure of the Lion near the Scales (which is not the zodiacal Lion) is\n"
"the constellation Centaurus [#1].\n"
" * There are two Shooters: one human with two legs, one centaur-like with four\n"
"legs. The centaur-like shooter is Sagittarius from the (Babylonian) zodiac, the\n"
"human bow-shooter represents the two constellations \"Bow\" and \"Arrow\", located\n"
"in the modern constellation Canis Maior (the \"Arrow\" includes Sirius) [#4].\n"
"\n"
"Earlier constellations are more problematic, but some indications exist that\n"
"some modern zodiac signs are very ancient indeed [#2][#3][#4][#13], although\n"
"the constellations did change significantly over time [#3][#13][#4].\n"
"\n"
"The Egyptians recognized five planets and called them the \"stars that knew no\n"
"rest\" or (more ancient way) \"eyes of [god] Horus\". Their movement across the\n"
"heavens reminded the Egyptians of five gods sailing across the sky in their\n"
"solar barque (boat). The planet now known as Jupiter was called \"Horus Who\n"
"Limits the Two Lands\"; Mars was \"Horus of the Horizon\"; Mercury was \"Sebegu\",\n"
"associated with Set; Saturn was \"Horus the Bull of the Sky\"; and Venus was \"the\n"
"God of the Morning\" [#8]."
msgstr ""
"Keyakinan bahwa bintang-bintang dapat mempengaruhi nasib manusia tampaknya tidak sampai ke Mesir sampai periode Ptolemeus. Kuil Hathor di Denderah berasal dari zaman Ptolemeus (mungkin abad pertama SM) dan menampilkan peta simbolik langit yang indah dan besar dalam gaya lukisan Mesir.\n"
"\n"
"Ini menyediakan dua versi: yang berbentuk lingkaran [#10] dan yang berbentuk persegi panjang [#11]. \"Zodiak\" persegi panjang dari Denderah menunjukkan urutan figur Mesir di sebelah satu set bintang simbolis yang menunjukkan berapa banyak bintang yang membentuk setiap rasi bintang. Lingkaran \"zodiak\" mengatur angka-angka ini seolah-olah mereka ditempatkan di langit.\n"
"\n"
"![](dendera_zodiac.webp) Salah satu penggambaran pertama \"zodiak\" Dendera, yang diproduksi oleh insinyur-arkeolog Prosper Jollois dan Edouard Devilliers pada abad ke-19. Sosok besar di sebelah kanan adalah Dewi Surga, Nut. Pertama kali diterbitkan dalam: Description de l'Égypte Antiquités, v. 4 [#12]\n"
"{: .img_and_caption  }\n"
"\n"
"Rasi bintang ini menyimpang dalam penamaan dan penggambaran dari gaya khas Yunani:\n"
"\n"
" * Kanker, Kepiting, diwakili oleh Kumbang Scarab.\n"
" * Biduk tidak disebut Beruang tetapi \"Kaki Depan Banteng\" mengacu pada Kaki Depan Dewa Seth, konstelasi Mesir kuno\n"
" * Sosok Singa di dekat Timbangan (yang bukan Singa zodiak) adalah konstelasi Centaurus [#1].\n"
" * Ada dua Penembak: satu manusia dengan dua kaki, satu seperti centaur dengan empat kaki. Penembak mirip centaur adalah Sagitarius dari zodiak (Babel), penembak busur manusia mewakili dua rasi bintang \"Busur\" dan \"Panah\", yang terletak di rasi modern Canis Maior (\"Panah\" termasuk Sirius) [#4].\n"
"\n"
"Rasi bintang sebelumnya lebih bermasalah, tetapi ada beberapa indikasi bahwa beberapa tanda zodiak modern memang sangat kuno [#2][#3][#4][#13], meskipun rasi bintang memang berubah secara signifikan dari waktu ke waktu [#3][#13][#4].\n"
"\n"
"Orang Mesir mengenali lima planet dan menyebut mereka \"bintang yang tidak mengenal istirahat\" atau (lebih kuno) \"mata [dewa] Horus\". Pergerakan mereka melintasi langit mengingatkan orang Mesir akan lima dewa yang berlayar melintasi langit dengan solar barque (perahu) mereka. Planet yang sekarang dikenal sebagai Jupiter disebut \"Horus yang Membatasi Dua Daratan\"; Mars adalah \"Horus of the Horizon\"; Merkurius adalah \"Sebegu\", terkait dengan Set; Saturnus adalah \"Horus si Banteng Langit\"; dan Venus adalah \"Dewa Pagi\" [#8]."

