"Ilustrasi dibuat oleh Antonio Gumercindo Taques dos Santos (Ticão) dan [Youssif Ganthous Filho](mailto:youssif@gmail.com).\n"
"\n"
"Adaptasi teknis: tim Stellarium"

# tupi sky culture name
msgid "Tupi-Guarani"
msgstr "Tupi-Guarani"

# tupi sky culture introduction section in markdown format
msgid ""
"Tupi-Guarani is a name given to a family of languages spoken by the indigenous\n"
"peoples of Brazil and other South American countries."
msgstr ""
"Tupi-Guarani adalah nama yang diberikan kepada keluarga bahasa yang "
"digunakan oleh penduduk asli Brasil dan negara-negara Amerika Selatan "
"lainnya."

# tupi sky culture description section in markdown format
msgid ""
"As with many cultures, constellations were identified and used to help keep\n"
"track of the seasons and predict the seasonal variations which affect daily\n"
"life. In the book _Histoire de la Mission de Pères Capucins en l'Isle de\n"
"Maragnan et terres circonvoisines_, published in Paris, 1614, it is stated that\n"
"the Tupi people identified some thirty constellations but the book only details\n"
"seven."
msgstr ""
"Seperti banyak budaya, rasi bintang diidentifikasi dan digunakan untuk "
"membantu melacak musim dan memprediksi variasi musiman yang memengaruhi "
"kehidupan sehari-hari. Dalam buku _Histoire de la Mission de Pères Capucins "
"en l'Isle de Maragnan et terres circonvoisines_, yang diterbitkan di Paris, "
"1614, disebutkan bahwa orang Tupi mengidentifikasi sekitar tiga puluh rasi "
"bintang tetapi buku itu hanya merinci tujuh."

# tupi sky culture references section in markdown format
msgid ""
" - [#1]: The Tupi People. [Wikipedia article](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tupi_people)\n"
" - [#2]: The Brazilian Indigenous Constellations by Germano Bruno Afonso (Portugese). [PDF](http://www.telescopiosnaescola.pro.br/indigenas.pdf)"
msgstr ""
" - [#1]: Orang Tupi. [Artikel Wikipedia](http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tupi_people)\n"
" - [#2]: Rasi Bintang Pribumi Brasil oleh Germano Bruno Afonso (Portugis). [PDF](http://www.telescopiosnaescola.pro.br/indigenas.pdf)"

# tupi sky culture authors section in markdown format
